issues.description: The problem statement specifies a parameterless method `checkOrderReady(): void`, but the solution defines and uses `checkOrderReady(boolean enableLogging)`. This signature mismatch will confuse students when they implement or invoke the method according to the specification.
issues.suggested_fix: Change the solution to implement `public void checkOrderReady()` (no parameters) to match the specification, optionally delegating to an internal method for logging if needed.
